Description: Male ( holotype ) (
Fig. 2
). Total length 3.67 . Prosoma 1.68 long, 1.63 wide; opisthosoma 1.99 long, 1.78 wide. Carapace yellowish brown, pear­shaped, slightly longer than wide, and covered with some small setae. Cephalic region rather dark brown, thoracic region with some brown spots. Both eye rows recurved. Diameters of eyes: AME 0.05 , ALE 0.13 , PME 0.08 , PLE 0.13 . Distances between eyes: AME–AME 0.10 , AME–ALE 0.08 , PME–PME 0.13 , PME–PLE 0.10 , ALE–PLE 0.15 . MOA 0.25 long, anterior width 0.15 , posterior width 0.30 . Bases of the lateral eye tubercle separated. Clypeus furnished with five long spiniform setae, height equal to the diameter of PLE, yellowish brown. Chelicerae brown, rather small and narrow, with scopulae on both margins of fang furrow; three promarginal teeth, of these the proximal one largest, and four retromarginal teeth with the distal one largest (
Fig. 4
). Maxillae and labium yellowish brown. Sternum yellowish brown, posterior margin narrow and extending between coxae IV.

Female (one paratype ) (
Fig. 1
). Total length 4.16 . Prosoma 1.95 long, 1.90 wide; opisthosoma 3.20 long, 3.15 wide. Diameters of eyes: AME 0.05 , ALE 0.13 , PME 0.08 , PLE 0.13 . Distances between eyes: AME­ALE 0.08 , AME­AME 0.10 , PME­PLE 0.10 , PME­PME 0.13 , ALE­PLE 0.15 . MOA 0.25 long, anterior width 0.15 , posterior width 0.30 . Eye tubercles of ALE and PLE separated.

Posterior half of dorsum with four brown spots, chelicerae (
Fig. 3
) and other characters as in male. Epigyne (
Figs. 5–6
) small, hood absent; copulatory openings clearly visible; spermathecae distinctly reniform.
